#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn2.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Anāthapiṇḍikavagga "
msgstr "2. With Anāthapiṇḍika "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Subrahmasutta "
msgstr "17. With Subrahmā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.123, sc1
msgctxt "sn2.17:1.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho subrahmā devaputto bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Standing to one side, the god Subrahmā addressed the Buddha in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.54, sc2
msgctxt "sn2.17:2.1"
msgid "“Niccaṃ utrastamidaṃ cittaṃ, "
msgstr "“This mind is always anxious, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: niccaṃ ubbiggamidaṃ → niccamubbiggamidaṃ (s1-3) | ubbiggidaṃ (mahāsatipaṭṭhānasuttavaṇṇanāyaṃ)
msgctxt "sn2.17:2.2"
msgid "niccaṃ ubbiggamidaṃ mano; "
msgstr "this mind is always stressed "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: kicchesu → kiccesu (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn2.17:2.3"
msgid "Anuppannesu kicchesu, "
msgstr "about stresses that haven’t arisen "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.17:2.4"
msgid "atho uppatitesu ca; "
msgstr "and those that have. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.17:2.5"
msgid "Sace atthi anutrastaṃ, "
msgstr "If there is a state free of anxiety, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.17:2.6"
msgid "taṃ me akkhāhi pucchito”ti. "
msgstr "please answer my question.” "

# NOTE: Further to BB’s notes on this, SA 596 seems to pass over bojjha, while SA2 181 has 智慧者, which appears to means one with buddhi.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: bojjhā tapasā → bojjhaṅgā tapasā (bj) | bojjhaṅgatapasā (s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.17:3.1"
msgid "“Nāññatra bojjhā tapasā, "
msgstr "“Not without understanding and austerity, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.17:3.2"
msgid "nāññatrindriyasaṃvarā; "
msgstr "not without restraining the sense faculties, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.17:3.3"
msgid "Nāññatra sabbanissaggā, "
msgstr "not without letting go of everything, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.17:3.4"
msgid "sotthiṃ passāmi pāṇinan”ti. "
msgstr "do I see safety for living creatures.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn2.17:4.1"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. … "

msgctxt "sn2.17:4.2"
msgid "tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "The god vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
